title: Brian Mulroney, Canadian prime minister who shook up economy, dies at 84
description: Mr. Mulroney built ties with President Reagan as a fellow conservative but also criticized U.S. policies and raised alarms about climate change.

title: As besieged Gaza grows desperate, donors drop aid from the sky
description: Jordanian Air Force pilots dropped 33 tons of food and supplies on Gaza on Thursday — vital support for those it reaches, but not nearly enough to meet needs in the besieged enclave.

title: Chaotic aid delivery turns deadly as Israeli, Gazan officials trade blame
description: Palestinian officials and eyewitnesses blamed the incident, one of the deadliest of the Gaza war, on Israeli gunfire, while Israeli officials blamed a stampede.

title: Why the health of Catherine, Princess of Wales, attracts fascination
description: It’s perhaps partly because she has so often been the very picture of health and fitness that her absence from public life has stirred so much commentary.

title: Iran’s elections will decide a new parliament. Here’s what to know.
description: Voters on Friday will also choose members of the Assembly of Experts, the body that will select Iran’s next supreme leader.

title: Putin threatens nuclear response to NATO troops if they go to Ukraine
description: In a speech to Russia’s Federal Assembly, Russian President Vladimir Putin threatened strikes against the West if there are attacks on Russian territory.

title: ‘Wounded Child, No Surviving Family’: Gaza’s doctors spell out a crisis
description: Of the horrors faced by children in Gaza, losing family is the hardest, doctors say. They came up with the WCNSF term to ensure those children would be looked after.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Hunger in Gaza causing ‘mass killing of children in slow motion,’ NGO says
description: Starvation is happening while aid trucks are “literally sitting just a few miles away,” a Save the Children official said, blaming conflict and Israeli inspections.

title: Democrats grew more divided on Israeli-Palestinian conflict, poll shows
description: The Israeli-Palestinian conflict has become an increasingly polarized issue in America, adding a fraught U.S. election problem to a foreign policy problem.
